
The nsdbi module is a shared library for the naviserver web server which
supports loadable database drivers. Use this in conjunction with the
nsdbipg (postgres), nsdbimy (mysql) or nsdbilite (sqlite) modules
to access your database.

You will require a recent version of NaviServer (>= 2008-05-12).

  $ make NAVISERVER=/usr/local/ns
  $ make NAVISERVER=/usr/local/ns install


See sample-config.tcl for configuration examples.

See doc/html/nsdbi.html for documentation.

http://naviserver.sourceforge.net/hg/nsdbi/
